In the last segment, we dive into Indiaâ€™s growth story, from competition between states and infrastructure spending to unemployment, opportunities for young talent, and lessons we can take from China. Ruchir also explains what needs to change for India to rise as a true global power.

title: The Dark Truth About Silicon Carbon Batteries! ğŸª«
description:
In this video, we are telling you about the dark truth of Silicon Carbon batteries. Are they actually better than Lithium Ion Batteries? How does all brands optimise? and more. To test it, we took 16 smartphones from 13 different brands including both Silicon Carbon and Lithium Ion batteries. We included iPhone 16(3561mAh), Samsung Z Fold 7, Pixel 10, Nothing Phone 3, vivo X200 Pro, Xiaomi 15 Ultra, OnePlus 13, realme GT7, realme P4, OnePlus Nord CE5, OPPO K13, iQOO Neo 10, moto G86 Power, moto edge 60 fusion, vivo T4 with 7300mAh and lastly, we also added the biggest battery phone you can get in India, the POCO F7 with 7550mAh. 

All the phones were at 100% health and we did the following tests, Scrolling Instagram reels for an hour, watching YouTube for an hour, selfie video recording for an hour, Played games like Subway Surfers and Unicorn Evolution for an hour each, followed by Plex Movie Streaming, Google Maps Street View usage and YouTube Music Playback. 

The full test crossed 15 hours in total and watch the video fully to see which phone actually won the Ultimate Battery Drain Test.

description:
In Electronics, ACs, TVs above 32â€, monitors, projectors and even dish washers will now only have 18% GST instead of 28%, but unfortunately thereâ€™s no change for smartphones and laptops.

In auto sector, non-electric Cars less than 1200cc for petrol and 1500cc for diesel, and under 4000mm in length will also have GST reduced from 28 to 18%. And not just that, the bigger expensive cars will also get a bit cheaper because now theyâ€™re at 40% GST, which used to be around 48% earlier.

Daily Items like oil, shampoo, soaps, Ghee, Cheese, Bhujia and more are getting a GST cut from 18% to 5%. Plus, normal medicines and Glucometer is also down to 5% only.

Another great change is, Health and Life Insurance now have no GST at all and it also applies to 36 life saving medicines as well as student supplies like pencil, notebooks, maps and more.

The GST on Gyms, Salons, barber shops and yoga centers will also be 5% only.

Lastly, thereâ€™s now a 40% slab for luxury and sin items like Luxury Cars, Aerated drinks, and tobacco products.

These changes will roll out from 22nd Sept, so if you are going to make any big purchases thatâ€™ll benefit you, wait till then.
